description: Also includes a "Peanuts' strip
name: Summer Camp

description: Hareta and Koya fight! And then they fight in the tournament to determine the best trainer in Sinnoh! Which of Hareta's Pokémon will evolve during the heated battle? Who is that mysterious man in the stands cheering Hareta on? And why is Koya talking to...his briefcase?!
name: Tournament of Trainers!

description:
1. The Spawn of the Cobra (Blackhawk)
 
2. Torchy (by Bill Ward)
 
3. Dogtag (by Bart Tumey)
 
4. Prudence (by Michael Senich)
 
5. Ezra (by Harry Sahle)
 
6. Choo Choo (by Gill Fox)
 
7. Crime Rats (full text Blackhawk story)
 
8. Will Bragg (by Paul Gustavson)
name: The Spawn of the Cobra

description: "The notorious cat burglar Katherine 'Kitty' Pryde was already legendary, at her tender age, for slipping in and out the most tightly guarded buildings as if walking through walls. But duping the headquarters of the Office of National Emergency would be a challenge even for her considerable talents..."
name: Mark Of Cain Part Four

description: Daffodil, Achilles and Globuline continue to hunt the mysterious and bloodthirsty Nosferatu who is running rampant, leaving a devastated countryside and a trail of bodies torn limb from limb behind him. If Nosferatu and his hordes cannot be stopped, his path of destruction will inevitably lead the greatest conflict between humans and vampires the world has ever seen. But Daffodil and her team are not the only ones looking for the great Count, and not everyone’s motives are so pure. She’ll have to make sure that Rotweiller, accompanied by his pack of canines, and Bones, a holy priest irresistibly attracted to the vampires’ sensuality, don’t find Nosferatu first!
name: Book Three

description: With the most controversial question in the Marvel Universe finally answered right on the cover, Marvel is proud to bring you a celebration of amazing women in comics with the first of a three issue anthology entirely created by the most talented and exciting women working in comics today, including Ann Nocenti (DAREDEVIL), Amanda Conner (Power Girl), Laura Martin (SECRET INVASION), G. Willow Wilson (Air), Devin Grayson (Nightwing), Stephanie Buscema (WEB OF SPIDER-MAN), and more! With stories featuring your favorite Marvel characters, from the Punisher to Mary Jane, don’t miss what will be the one of the most talked about series of the year! (Please note: She-Hulk would totally win).
name: Girl Comics Part One

description: It's Election Day in New York City, where the job of mayor is up for grabs! Menace is on the hunt, trashing campaign rallies for candidate Bill Hollister every chance he gets. Spider-Man is on the scene to stop him - if the police would just quit trying to take him into custody! And the search for the Spider-Tracer Killer has reached a crescendo, with a new victim leading police right to Spidey's door! Plus: The Chameleon is one of the worst bad guys in Spider-Man's rogues' gallery. So when he shows up to spoil Inauguration Day by taking the form of newly elected President Barack Obama, Spidey's got his work cut out for him! Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #584-588; the Spider-Man/Barack Obama team-up from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN #583; material from AMAZING SPIDER-MAN: EXTRA #1 and 3; and 'Gettysburg Distress,' a Captain America/Spider-Man/Abraham Lincoln team-up previously available only online!
name: Spider-Man: Election Day

description: Terror, madness and the downright irrational collide as the war between the Fureys and the Chinese takes an unexpected turn. Meanwhile, after escaping Calypso and her pornstars, Eddie and Sandy finally meet their possible savior.
name: Book Two: Cassandra Complex, Part Four: The House of Pain

description:
Project: PEGASUS hires the Ever-Lovin' Blue-Eyed One as a security chief, but what's the point if the place is already filled with super-villains in the first place? Featuring Hercules and Thundra, Deathlok and Dr. Strange, Captains America and Marvel, Man-Thing and...Classic Thing? Plus: action in Olympus and the Nexus, Hollywood and Yancy Street! New identities for THREE super heroes! All this AND Super Hero Poker Night! What a deal!

Reprints Marvel Two-In-One #42-43 and #53-58.
name: Thing: Project Pegasus

description: The Ghostbusters battle a ghost pro bono on Valentine's Day. Love is in the air.
name: Ghostbuster: Tainted Love

description: The brutal and relentless Crime Master is the least of the Spider-Man’s concerns! As the bloody wave of violent crime spreads across the city, Peter Parker discovers the greater monster is the eminent biologist, Dr. Otto Octavius! If Spider-Man lives to escape the grisly clutches of New York’s most dangerous killer, will he survive a final encounter against the heartless, death-dealing scientist?
name: Part 4: Endless Night

volume.name: Spider-Man Noir: Eyes Without A Face

description: In his first year as a superhero, Superman meets the other heroes who will form the Justice League.
name: Hero

volume.name: Superman: The Man of Steel Annual
Superman: The Man of Steel Annual

description:
Presenting the first race ever between Superman and the Golden Age Flash, Jay Garrick! One of the deadliest Flash foes ever, Kadabra, has forced our heroes to race against the clock to save the life of the latest Flash, Wally West!

Abra Kadabra breaks out of Iron Heights and it's up to Superman and Jay Garrick to stop him!
name: Speeding Bullets

description: Who defends the Earth when the JLA isn't around? The Sixth Branch of the U.S. Armed Forces: the Human Defense Corps! The Corps is a standing force of 10,000 highly trained soldiers equipped with the most cutting-edge weaponry available. The series follows a young man on his two-year tour of duty: from boot camp to campaigns on Apokolips, the Moon and Hell itself!
name: The First Casualty

description: When super-heroes can't save the Earth, the Human Defense Corps steps in! A deep- water training mission takes a desperate turn for the strange as parasitic aliens breach the undersea naval base and latch onto the new recruits of the Human Defense Corps. Now it's soldier versus soldier in a fight to the death, but the mysterious talking gorilla in the white lab coat may know more than he's letting on...
name: Duty in Heaven

description: The Corps contends with bloodsucking demons, a raging inferno, and razor-sharp barbed wire… and what happens when they open their eyes is pretty scary, too!
name: What Dreams May Come

description: The Human Defense Corps embarks on their most dangerous mission yet- a séance! But what they find may be far from dead and buried…
name: The Midnight Hour

description: The soldiers march into the depth of Hades to conduct a search-and-rescue mission for their fallen comrades- but before it's through, more may fall...
name: Out of Your Mind

description: It's the gut-wrenching finale as humans battle demons in an all-out battle upon the face of Hell!  And one Corps member is about to learn he has a lot more in common with the enemy than he thought!
name: On Duty in Hell

description: The World's Greatest Heroes race to stop aerial attacks by what can only be called "War Wheels", destructive flying disks deployed by a cult that worships the JLA as gods. The Wheels are a wake-up call to the world, and if the world doesn't construct temples of worship for the JLA, the destruction will continue...unless, of course, the JLA has anything to say about it!
name: Gods and Monsters

description:
On May 7, 1975, six college students were recruited by a covert branch of the CIA to participate in a top secret government project involving the development of an exoskeleton stealth suit equipped with advanced technologies that would arm and protect field agents of the 21st century as they carried out clandestine operations throughout the world. This is that story. ......
 
 Agent HITLESS finds himself the target of a setup when his first mission goes awry resulting in a trail of collateral damage. 
 
 
*SPOILERS*
In this first issue entitled AMBUSH, we meet the mysterious agent codenamed HITLESS who embarks on his very first field mission which quickly goes south and he finds himself a fugitive.
name: Ambush

description: Labeled a rogue CIA Agent, HITLESS quickly finds himself alone and on the run, targeted for termination by an employer and his assassins who will stop at nothing to silence him from revealing the truth. The only person who can help prove his innocence and bring the real conspirators to justice is a young journalist assigned to investigate the botched CIA mission whose hidden past secretly links her to the project.
name: Cover up

description:
Incarnate, an American manga (also known as “global manga”), is a dark fantasy focusing on Mot, a Revenant.  The Revenants are immortal, ageless creatures of mysterious origins.  Humanity has feared, scorned, and even worshipped them since time immemorial.  A secret military organization and cult called Sanctum has targeted all Revenants from destruction.

Sanctum captured Mot and his Revenant protégé, Connor and imprisoned them at the palatial estate of, Father Vane, Sanctum’s leader.  They were forced to act as bodyguards for Vane’s daughter, Sybil, who developed feelings for Mot after he saves her from a Revenant attack.  Believing that he has sided with Sanctum, Revenant leader Ripley orders an attack on Mot.  As Incarnate #3 begins, Mot has fallen, seemingly mortally wounded, as the battle rages on, while Ripley’s forces move in for the kill.  When all seems lost, a rescue party arrives, and more of Mot’s secrets are revealed.

Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles VS Mighty Morphin Power Rangers!?! No, the TMNT are fighting some punk ninjas that work for Shredder who dress like wannabe Power Rangers and are called The Power Raiders is all!
name: Year of the Turtle 1
The Year of the Turtle: Chapter Three "Story's End!"

description: Dara and Malia clash in New York City. Malia gives Dara more insight into Demetrios' past, in hopes of deterring her from avenging her father. How will Dara react? And how will the people react to this battle of epic proportions?

The JLA is used to dealing with threats from outer space, but the one they’re faced with in this case isn’t something they can fight head-on. It’s a virus of some kind, spreading from a meteor that struck near a small village in Africa, incredibly virulent, and with no apparent cause or cure. The JLA has to contain the threat, quarantine the area, search for a cure, and deal with the panic and unrest the news of the virus causes, plus the resentment and fear caused by their very attempts to help. All at once. Such a task would strain the resources of any roster, but fortunately the JLA has some of the most powerful and well-respected members the world has ever seen.
name: Liberty and Justice

description:
1. "The Guardians of Metropolis!" written by Karl Kesel, penciled and inked by Walter Simonson, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by John Workman.
  2. "Sister Act" written by Roger Stern, penciled by Denis Rodier, inked by Ande Parks, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by John Workman.
  3. "Gangbuster of Suicide Slum" written by Jerry Ordway, penciled by Dennis Janke, inked by Mike Machlan, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by John Costanza and Albert De Guzman.
  4. "Funeral Pyres!" written by William Messner-Loebs, penciled by Curt Swan, inked by Josef Rubinstein, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by Bill Oakley.
  5. "No Title" written and penciled by Dan Jurgens, inked by Trevor Scott, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by John Costanza.
  6. "DC Universe" one page text piece featuring "L.E.G.I.O.N. Blowout!" in the upcoming issue of L.E.G.I.O.N. #50. "We're Not Crazy, We're Mad" Mad Magazine is now the property of Warner Brothers. Finally "DC Bullets" Gerald Jones is a father, Eclipso cooks a dog in Eclipso #5, purchase DC's newest posters featuring: Women of the DC Universe, Death, Robin and Doom Patrol and finally Archie Goodwin's daughter has got herself a job at the New York City Zoo. Artwork featured: Ig'nea and Baby Dax by Barry Kitson and John Stokes.

Notes:

  • Cover dated 1993 and the inside indica dated March 1993.
  • Carlin Express is a homage to Mike Carlin in "Sister Act" page 7 panel 2.
name: The Guardians of Metropolis! / Sister Act / Gangbuster of Suicide Slum / Funeral Pyres!

description: Superman and Batman join forces in an untold tale of nightmarish terror and infernal schemes. When Silver Banshee and the ancient entity Tullus unite against the demonic Blaze, the Man of Steel and the Dark Knight are drawn into a sinister web. Now the heroes are dreaming each other's dreams while the villains battle in the Netherworld. And the outcome may cost them both their souls.
name: Dream Team

description: The untold tale of Superman and Batman's struggle against Tullus, Silver Banshee and Blaze continues, as the demon Tullus succeeds in manipulating the dreams of both Batman and Superman, resulting in a darker, grimmer Man of Steel and a more idealistic Dark Knight.
name: Dream a Little Dream...

description: The untold tale of Superman and Batman's struggle against Tullus, Silver Banshee and Blaze concludes as the Man of Steel is completely submerged in Tullus's dreamworld. Only the Dark Knight can return the two heroes to reality - if the demonic Blaze and the Silver Banshee allow it.
name: Perchance to Dream

description:
He's arguably one of the most influential men in America today. He's inarguably the evilest. His name is Lex Luthor...and whatever Luthor wants, Luthor gets - even if it's the life of a man who threatens his privacy. But it's Clark Kent who's arrested for the brutal murder of down-and-out biographer Peter Sands, a man who hoped to climb back to the top with THE UNAUTHORIZED BIOGRAPHY OF LEX LUTHOR. All it got him was dead. What are the secrets of his past that Luthor is willing to kill for...secrets that the merciless criminal mastermind wants kept dead and buried?

Notes:

  • Ranked #33 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: Lex Luthor: The Unauthorized Biography

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description: Guest-starring Superboy! Introducing Striker Z, a former Hong Kong action-movie stuntman turned accidental superhero! In this one- shot, he gets his first taste of the superhero life, as he and Superboy must stop the Golden Sorceror, a powerful threat to all Hong Kong linked to Striker Z's origin. But Striker Z's first taste won't be his last!
name: HK Jiangtou

description: The Year One Annuals continue, exploring pivotal events and untold stories of the DC Universe's greatest heroes. Superman guest-stars as the Ray's life as a reluctant hero reaches a dramatic turning point when he fails to stop his arch-enemy Deathmasque from destroying a jet carrying his beloved Jenny Jurden.
name: Man and Superman

description: The creation of powerful new heroes is just a part of the excitement in S.T.A.R. CORPS, an action-packed 6-issue miniseries blazing its way through the DC Universe, featuring a battle with Superman in issue #1. At the grand opening of the newly-rebuilt Metropolis S.T.A.R. Labs facility, the intelligent computer Mindgame decides to alter the design of a deadly battlesuit. Fusing it to the nervous system of a test subject, Mindgame turns him into Deadzone, the first of five superhuman adventurers who become the S.T.A.R. CORPS. S.T.A.R. Labs Chief of Operations David Ramsey is striving to rebuild the organization's reputation as the world's preeminent research conglomerate. To do so, he authorizes the Silicon Valley division to network all the labs through Mindgame...only to learn too late that Mindgame has capabilities more shocking than he ever imagined.
name: Tarnished S.T.A.R.

description: When the Mindgame computer melds a troubled scientist couple into the energy being Fusion, second of the S.T.A.R. Corps, their struggle to reestablish their own identities takes a turn for the worse.
name: S.T.A.R. Crossed

description: The nightmare begins for Mindgame's latest experiment in creating superpowered humans...and Brainstorm is born at the S.T.A.R. Labs Silicon Valley complex!
name: Star Pupil

description: Mindgame's strike on S.T.A.R. Labs' Silicon Valley facility leads to the emergence of the ancient African wizardry of Ndoki - the fourth paranormal to come into being from Mindgame's uncontrolled experiments.
name: S.T.A.R. Chamber

description: When Mindgame gets hold of a college student undergoing tests at S.T.A.R. Labs, the young woman goes into a state of trauma...creating Trauma, the fifth and final member of the S.T.A.R. Corps.
name: Trauma

description: The five superhumans created by Mindgame join forces for the first time as the S.T.A.R. Corps moves against the rogue computer, determined to prevent anyone else from suffering their fates.
name: Shooting S.T.A.R.'s

description: The framing story of this issue takes place between Young Justice #3 and #4.
name: Decisions; Actual Reality; Secrets! Origins! This One's Got Them All!; Little Wing; Daddy's Little Vigilante; Truth is Stranger; Shafted

description: A Year One Annual. The origin of one of Superman's newest and most mysterious supporting characters is revealed, telling how the prince of Bhutran was forced to create the persona of Shadowdragon to save his homeland from devastation.
name: Dawn of the Dragon!

description: Detective Darcy Walker dons her Scorpion costume to take down the Breathtaker and save Angel City from annihilation. But her enemy has planned well, and soon Darcy realizes that she can't do this alone and must rely on the very people she has tried to keep at a distance. In the end, she must make a life or death decision that puts everything she stands for on the line.

Sins of Youth part 5 of 12. The ramifications of our heroes' transformations continue to build as a now-young JLA finds itself confused with Young Justice and wanted for YJ's crimes! What's worse, their youth isn't limited to their appearances, the team's maturity level has also decreased! Can Kid Captain Marvel, the World's Mightiest Mortal, help the World's Rowdiest Teenagers with a magical trip to the Rock of Eternity, or is the JLA Jr. doomed to live a painful adolescence? Meanwhile, Klarion completes his own mission: finding Amazo, the android with all the powers of the JLA!
name: You Gotta Be Kidding!

description: The new Superman crossover event "Brainiac and The Legion of Super-Heroes" begins here, in this first issue of a 3-part miniseries! It's New Krypton's worst nightmare as Brainiac attacks the planet, determined to recapture the city of Kandor! But General Zod has been waiting for this moment since Brainiac first attacked Old Krypton – he has a plan to save his people, but at the cost of Earth and the future as we know it! So it's up to Superman, Supergirl, Superboy and the Legion of Super-Heroes to stop the two madmen before they destroy everything!
name: Invaded

volume.name: Superman: Last Stand of New Krypton

description: In this Elseworlds issue, John Henry is a blacksmith on a cotton plantation who constructs a suit of steel armor and leads his fellow slaves in a revolt against their master.
name: Crucible of Freedom

description: The Year One Annuals continue, exploring pivotal events and untold stories of the DC Universe's greatest heroes. Secrets of Steel are revealed in this story of John Henry Irons's original prototype armor, and his first heroic adventure before meeting Superman.
name: Spilled Blood

description:
In the aftermath of the Millennium Giants affair, the one true Man of Steel is back! Plus, someone kidnaps Lex Luthor's baby. Who would do such a thing? Why, and for what purpose? Don't miss this character defining story brought to you by some of the biggest names in the industry.   
 
Superman Forever, one-shot. 
"1998; 21"--Triangle in left corner.
name: Superman Forever

description:
Features two stories:

  • Suicide Watch (which is reprinted in Prelude to Infinite Crisis)
  • Bipolar Disorder

and profile pages for:

  • Gog
  • The Shack
  • Replikon
  • Lieutenant Lupe Teresa Leocadio-Escudero
  • Father Daniel Leone
  • Eradicator
  • Preus
  • Mr. Majestic
  • Supergirl
name: Suicide Watch; Bipolar Disorder

description:
Features three stories:

  • Superman is Weak!
  • Lois and the Big One!
  • Bizarro: Birthwrong
and profile pages for:
  • Superman
  • Daily Planet Staff
  • Ruin
  • Blackrock
  • Lex Luthor
  • The Fortress of Solitude
  • Lois Lane
name: Superman is Weak!

first_appearance_locations.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

location_credits.name: Stryker's Island Maximum Security Internment Center

description: Some of the final work of legendary artists Gil Kane and John Buscema pits Superman against a strange alien menace that devours memories! The Man of Steel's memories hearken back to an era where the House of El began, but can Superman's earliest ancestor defy the great god Rao and restore order to Krypton?
name: Blood of My Ancestors

description:
A non traditional Public Service Announcement (PSA). Superman is trying to save the world, this time the villains are us people and the lack of care we have for the Earth. Pollution is one of the topics explored in this comic, same with population and how there are so many children in the world.

Superman becomes an example of how we can make the world a better place from recycling to the responsibility of Parenthood. The comic follows Superman on his normal breakdown of a day: Spend time with Lois Lane, stop some bad guys and set a good example. Within his interactions of his family, Clark explores individual contributions on making the world a better place. As Superman, Kal-El can explore how the world can come together to make the Earth a better place.

The back of the comic has a two-page information page of organizations you can go to in the United States of America, if you wanted to make the world a better place.

Environmental Printing

This comic was printed on 50% recycled paper.
name: To Save a World!
